line_1: Patience is sorrow's salve; what can't be cur'd,
line_2: So Donald right areeds, must be endur'd.

line_1: But if they listen, they are cur'd.
line_2: Your fame's by your own noise obscur'd,

line_1: And spite of the imp I was cur'd.
line_2: They laugh'd at the ills I endur'd;

line_1: Pains which are seldom felt, and never cur'd!
line_2: Say, that thy wretched victim long endur'd,

line_1: Some hopeless passion, never to be cur'd:
line_2: Some lingring malady for years endur'd,

line_1: Well, be it so — What can't be cur'd,
line_2: The Proverb says, must be endur'd.

line_1: But by the jest was cured.
